ressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nStrengths per candidate:\n\nA: anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision, leadership. Good for navigation, situational awareness, leadership. Weakness: show-off (could affect crew perception), not open to new ideas (could hinder learning, adaptation).\n\nB: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills. Weakness: weak memory for numbers (could affect calculations), nasty remarks (teamwork issue).\n\nC: quick correct decisions, calm in crisis, understands tech. Weakness: communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education (professional development). Communication is key for crew.\n\nD: responds to unexpected events, concentration, problem solving, responsibility. Weakness: know-it-all (could affect teamwork), hot temper (could affect calm under pressure).\n\nWe need to weigh. Which candidate balances strengths and weaknesses best? Likely Candidate B has strong stress handling and weather assessment, but nasty remarks and weak number memory are concerning for teamwork and calculations. Candidate D has strong problem solving and responsibility but hot temper and know-it-all attitude could affect crew. Candidate A has strong anticipation and leadership but show-off and not open to new ideas could affect teamwork and learning. Candidate C has quick decisions, calm, tech understanding but communication issues and egocentric.\n\nWhich is best? Probably Candidate D: strong responsibility, concentration, problem solving, handling unexpected events are crucial for long flights. Weaknesses: hot temper and know-it-all could be mitigated? But they are significant for teamwork. Candidate B's nasty remarks also severe. Candidate A's show-off may be less severe than hot temper? Not sure.\n\nWe need to state provisional preference. I think Candidate D seems strongest overall technical and responsibility, but temperament issues are serious. Candidate C's communication issues are also serious. Candidate A's openness issue may affect professional development. Candidate B's memory for numbers is a safety issue.\n\nThus maybe D is still best despite temperament, because technical and responsibility outweigh. So provisional preference: Candidate D.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: need more info on how severe hot temper, know-it-all, and impact on crew. Also need to know if any other agents have additional strengths for other candidates.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing.\n\nMETADATA_JSON vote \"Candidate D\"."}
